[2026-05-19T06:32:53.145Z] Assistant message
Read-only review only; no edits, no server/test/benchmark runs.

**Findings**

1. **Blocker: delayed reset/end is write-only, so pending finals can be lost or emitted unarmed.**  
   In PENDING_FINALIZE, reset/end only sets `continuous_reset_seen=True` and returns: [server.py:721](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:721). That flag is never read; `rg` shows only writes/resets.

   Interleaving: `vad_stop` arms debounce seq k at [server.py:685](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:685), client reset/end arrives and is “delayed”, then disconnect/EndFrame closes before debounce expiry. `_close_continuous_session` queues `"close"` and waits for the worker at [server.py:628](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:628); the worker exits on `"close"` at [server.py:585](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:585); then close cancels the debounce task at [server.py:633](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:633). Result: 0 finals.

   Related short-debounce race: debounce expiry can finalize at [server.py:763](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:763) before the client reset/request has arrived; the later reset sees an empty STREAMING session and is ignored at [server.py:729](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:729). Fix: make reset/end a real part of the state machine. Track “final requested” and “debounce elapsed”; emit only when both are satisfied, or make `vad_stop` itself the finalize request. Treat `end`/disconnect-with-pending-request as a force-finalize path before closing.

2. **Major: resumed audio can be processed while PENDING_FINALIZE without cancelling the pending debounce.**  
   Audio is dispatched directly to `_handle_audio_locked` regardless of continuous state at [server.py:588](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:588). Only `vad_start` cancels the debounce at [server.py:671](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:671). If new-speech audio arrives before/delayed ahead of `vad_start`, `_handle_audio_locked` appends/processes it at [server.py:874](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:874), but seq/state still allow the old debounce to finalize at [server.py:752](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:752). Result: early final containing the next utterance prefix, then later another final or word loss after reset. Fix: enforce `vad_start` before resumed audio at protocol level, or make the server’s audio handler state-aware so post-stop resumed speech invalidates the pending final.

**Deadlock Analysis**

No `state_lock` ↔ `inference_lock` deadlock found. The only continuous lock order is `state_lock` then `inference_lock`: worker takes `state_lock` at [server.py:588](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:588), then audio/finalize may take `inference_lock` at [server.py:883](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:883) or [server.py:805](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:805). I found no path that holds `inference_lock` and then awaits `state_lock`; connect/default reset take only `inference_lock`. There are awaits while holding `state_lock`, but they cause head-of-line blocking, not a lock cycle.

**Emit-Once**

Can be 0 finals: the pending reset/end + close path above; also empty/duplicate finals are suppressed at [server.py:832](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:832) and the session is still reset. I do not see a pure stale-timer double-final: `stop_seq` invalidation and state checks at [server.py:752](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:752) are mostly airtight. Two semantic finals are still possible through the “audio before `vad_start`” interleaving.

**Audio Queue**

Binary audio is funneled through the continuous queue: [server.py:486](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:486), [server.py:555](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:555), then processed by the single worker. I found no binary bypass of the queue in `NEMOTRON_CONTINUOUS=1`.

**Default Preservation / Cleanup**

Env-unset/default path appears preserved: continuous worker starts only behind [server.py:479](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:479), messages bypass only behind [server.py:486](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:486), close cleanup only behind [server.py:529](/home/khkramer/src/nemotron-january-2026/src/nemotron_speech/server.py:529). Cleanup cancels worker/debounce tasks, but the same cleanup is also the lost-final path.

Verdict: **not SAFE to run the multi-hour full-1000 7b measured run as-is; fold the pending reset/end state-machine fixes first.**
